        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Paul, being grieved",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The Greek verb is somewhat stronger, and signifies “to be thoroughly worn out with annoyance.” It is used (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 4:2",
        "children": []
      },
